<center>
   <br></br>
   <h1>Scriptlets</h1>
   <br>
</center>
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>Scriptlets allow for Java code to be directly embedded into a JSP
page.</li>
   <li>They are permitted to produce output to the page, but do not
necessarily have to.</li>
   <ul>
      <li>If a scriptlet is to produce output to a page, it uses the
implicit "out" object.</li>
   </ul>
</ul>
<br><br>
<p>Example of a scriptlet:</p>
<font color="red">
   <p>The current date is:
      <br>&lt% out.println(new java.util.Date()); %></p>
</font>
</font>
</html>

